org.chronos.chronosphere.api

Interface ChronoSphereBranchManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChronoSphereBranchManagerImpl

    public interface ChronoSphereBranchManager
    The branch manager is responsible for creating and maintaining branches in a ChronoSphere repository.

    You can get an instance of this class via ChronoSphere.getBranchManager().

      • createBranch

        SphereBranch createBranch(java.lang.String branchName)
        Creates a new child of the master branch with the given name.

        This will use the head revision as the base revision for the new branch.

        Parameters:
        branchName - The name of the new branch. Must not be null. Must not refer to an already existing branch. Branch names must be unique.
        Returns:
        The newly created branch. Never null.
        See Also:
        createBranch(String, long), createBranch(String, String), createBranch(String, String, long)

      • createBranch

        SphereBranch createBranch(java.lang.String branchName,
                          long branchingTimestamp)
        Creates a new child of the master branch with the given name.
        Parameters:
        branchName - The name of the new branch. Must not be null. Must not refer to an already existing branch. Branch names must be unique.
        branchingTimestamp - The timestamp at which to branch away from the master branch. Must not be negative. Must be less than or equal to the timestamp of the latest commit on the master branch.
        Returns:
        The newly created branch. Never null.
        See Also:
        createBranch(String), createBranch(String, String), createBranch(String, String, long)

      • createBranch

        SphereBranch createBranch(java.lang.String parentName,
                          java.lang.String newBranchName)
        Creates a new child of the given parent branch with the given name.

        This will use the head revision of the given parent branch as the base revision for the new branch.

        Parameters:
        parentName - The name of the parent branch. Must not be null. Must refer to an existing branch.
        newBranchName - The name of the new child branch. Must not be null. Must not refere to an already existing branch. Branch names must be unique.
        Returns:
        The newly created branch. Never null.
        See Also:
        createBranch(String), createBranch(String, long), createBranch(String, String, long)
